news.title: SC orders action against building constructed illegally in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: The Supreme Court has ordered the Thiruvananthapuram city corporation to take strict action against a four-storey commercial building owner, G Mohandas, for violating construction rules. Mohandas's appeal to quash criminal proceedings was dismissed, with the court upholding the Kerala High Court's decision.

news.title: Property tax notices issued despite Ghaziabad civic body's repeal, councillors stage protest
news.para: Ghaziabad Municipal Corporation (GMC) councillors protested against hiked property tax notices issued to residents despite the board's decision to repeal the proposal, effective since April 1. Councillors claim the notices violate municipal acts and demand access to meeting minutes confirming the repeal.

news.title: Urban local bodies across Uttar Pradesh begin house tax recovery drive
news.para: Urban local bodies across Uttar Pradesh have initiated a special drive from July 15 to July 31 to recover pending house taxes from property owners. The initiative aims to cover over 55 lakh properties in 17 key cities, targeting a revenue of Rs 1,862 crore.

news.title: Notices to 783 buildings in CRZ areas, 44 razed: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: Mumbai authorities issued notices to 783 buildings in coastal zones. Forty-four illegal structures have been demolished. A special investigation team arrested 23 people in connection with forged maps.

news.title: Big relief for Bengaluru property owners: B-Khatas to be treated as A-Khatas
news.para: The Karnataka Cabinet has approved the regularization of B-Khata properties in Bengaluru issued up to September 30, 2024, granting them A-Khata status and access to essential civic amenities. This decision aims to bring discipline to property development and resolve long-standing legal ambiguities.

news.title: About 40 developers yet to pay ₹261 crore deposit for transit tenements: CAG
news.para: A CAG report revealed that Mhada allotted 3,357 transit tenements to 43 private developers for redevelopment projects initiated around 25 years ago. As of March 2022, many developers still possessed these tenements, with Rs 261.14 crore in outstanding dues yet to be recovered from 40 of them. Only three developers cleared their dues.

news.title: Only one of eight city divisions gave dilapidated buildings' list: CAG
news.para: Mumbai authorities are facing scrutiny for their lax approach to dilapidated buildings. Only one of eight divisions submitted a list of dangerous structures, and even that list was flawed, containing buildings already demolished or under redevelopment. This negligence raises concerns, especially given past collapses and fatalities.

news.title: Delhi HC urges DDA to rebuild trust with Signature View Apartments residents
news.para: Delhi High Court is trying to resolve the Signature View Apartments issue. There is a trust problem between the DDA and residents. Residents refuse to leave unsafe towers. The court asks DDA to build trust by paying owed rentals. DDA must provide payment details. The court is reviewing a previous order about demolition and additional flats.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Plan for 100 cement plants on Parsik hill to be probed
news.para: The Union Forest Protection Division has ordered an investigation into proposed ready-mix concrete plants in Navi Mumbai's Parsik Hill, following environmentalists' concerns about air and noise pollution. These plants are planned for former quarry sites, raising fears about worsening air quality in the rapidly developing urban area. Previous quarrying on 260 hectares was stopped in 2017.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body flooded with queries amid 5% property tax hike
news.para: Ludhiana residents inquired about property tax after a 5% hike announcement, but officials clarified the increase has been annual since 2021, based on a state government letter. This hike allows the state to borrow more from the central government.

news.title: Short-term rentals in Noida under scanner as highrise ‘b&bs’ proliferate
news.para: Noida authorities are investigating short-term rentals in residential societies. Complaints include noise, drug use, and illegal commercial activities. District Magistrate Manish Verma has ordered a probe into these properties. Concerns are rising about compliance with the Sarai Act and excise rules. A multi-agency team will survey societies and submit a report.

news.title: Odisha RERA reforms to add to buyers’ interests
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) is undergoing reforms to better protect homebuyers and streamline operations. Key changes include integrating local enforcement and mandating district collectors to review RERA provisions monthly and report illegal constructions.

news.title: RERA to oversee real estate registrations in Meghalaya
news.para: Meghalaya's Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA) will now supervise the registration of real estate projects, promoters, and agents, as notified by the government in 2020. This aims to establish a transparent and accountable real estate sector, urging all developers and agents to register to avoid penalties and foster trust.

news.title: Arrest those putting even single brick despite construction ban in Chandi Chowk area: SC
news.para: The Supreme Court has strongly condemned unauthorized constructions in Delhi's Chandni Chowk, despite an existing ban. The court directed Delhi Police to arrest anyone involved, even those "putting even a brick". Patrolling parties must be deployed to halt illegal construction and seal properties.

news.title: Now, 5% green cover must for new town planning schemes in Ahmedabad
news.para: Ahmedabad is poised for a green transformation as the AMC unveils policies mandating green spaces in new town planning schemes, including urban forests using the Miyawaki method. The initiative, set to launch on July 19, also focuses on good construction practices, increased penalties for illegal tree cutting, and the development of diverse green infrastructure across the city.

news.title: Highrise buildings in Prayagraj to undergo mandatory structural safety audits
news.para: Prayagraj introduces mandatory structural safety audits for high-rise buildings exceeding 15 meters, prompted by safety concerns and past fire incidents. Buildings must undergo audits 10 years post-construction, then every five years. Owners or RWAs must address identified risks promptly, or authorities will conduct repairs at their expense, ensuring stricter enforcement and improved safety standards.

news.title: Nagpur civic body penalises 4,890 for occupying public spaces with building material
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation cracked down on illegal encroachments. Over the past six months, NMC acted against 4,658 individuals and 232 builders. They were penalized for placing construction materials on public spaces. The civic body collected Rs 1.16 crore in penalties. The campaign aimed to keep Nagpur clean and pedestrian-friendly. The drive will continue to prevent public disruption.

news.title: Godrej Properties' COO and CEO-Mumbai region resigns
news.para: Godrej Properties sees leadership changes. Vikas Singhal, COO, and Priyansh Kapoor, Zonal CEO-MMR, resign. Amitesh Shah will succeed Kapoor. Sandeep Navlakhe will replace Singhal.

news.title: Lloyds’ promoter family buys apartments in south Mumbai’s Altamount Road for ₹227 crore
news.para: Ravi Agarwal and his family, part of the Lloyds Group promoters, have acquired six sea-view luxury apartments in Mumbai's Kalpataru Prive for over Rs 227 crore. The deal, valued at Rs 1.27 lakh per sq ft, includes a seven-bedroom duplex and 24 car parking slots. This transaction reaffirms Altamount Road's status as a prime residential location.

news.title: Lucknow development body's bylaws for compounding maps to benefit many
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is set to approve compounding maps under the new Model Building Construction and Development Bylaws and Model Zoning Regulation-2025, benefiting property owners who previously constructed buildings without approval.
